<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="370" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,223,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The relatively large body size (male body length 
<number box="[880,993,223,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="6.845" valueMax="6.88" valueMin="6.81">6.81–6.88</number>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1017,1110,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 20" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1737,1759]" captionTargetBox="[225,1362,417,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[209,1378,409,1716]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 20. Habitus of Metrocoris spp. (apterous males). 13 – 16. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (13: Qingchen mountain; 14: Laojun mountain; 15: Xinmin village; 16: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 17. M. astictus sp. nov.; 18. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 19. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 20. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269715/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">Figs. 18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1122,1154,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,524,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1403,517,1753]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 28. Photographs of bodies of apterous morph of Metrocoris spp. in dorsal view (males). 21 – 24. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (21: Qingchen mountain; 22: Laojun mountain; 23: Xinmin village; 24: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 25. M. astictus sp. nov.; 26. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 27. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 28. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269716/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">26</figureCitation>
); longitudinal dark stripe on the mesopleuron running at least 
<number box="[566,580,260,284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[589,601,260,284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="3.0">3</number>
of its length, and very close to anterior margin; fore femora bearing only with a subapical indentation and a small single apical tooth (
<figureCitation box="[822,904,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[178,1406,1766,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[173,1413,1764,1921]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Line drawings of fore legs of Metrocoris spp. (males) in lateral view. 39. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 40. M. astictus sp. nov.; 41. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 42. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 43. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269718/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">
Fig. 
<number box="[873,904,296,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
); the unmodified inner surface of the fore tibiae (
<figureCitation box="[159,245,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[178,1406,1766,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[173,1413,1764,1921]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Line drawings of fore legs of Metrocoris spp. (males) in lateral view. 39. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 40. M. astictus sp. nov.; 41. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 42. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 43. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269718/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,245,332,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
); the male proctiger with a pair of blackish dots laterally (
<figureCitation box="[922,1008,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 58" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1297,1319]" captionTargetBox="[184,1395,207,1269]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[164,1424,193,1276]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 58. Photographs of abdominal segment VIII, pygophore and proctiger of Metrocoris spp. (males). 44, 49, 54. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 45, 50, 55. M. astictus sp. nov.; 46, 51, 56. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 47, 52, 57. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 48, 53, 58. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269719/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">
Fig. 
<number box="[976,1008,332,357]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="56.0">56</number>
</figureCitation>
); the typically falciform shape of the paramere (
<figureCitation box="[270,363,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 59 – 66" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,1438,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[175,1411,1430,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 59 – 66. Paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males) in external view. 59 – 62. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (59: Qingchen mountain; 60: Laojun mountain; 61: Xinmin village; 62: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 63. M. astictus sp. nov.; 64. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 65. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 66. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269720/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">Figs. 64</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[375,407,368,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 83" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,887,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[205,1381,876,1821]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 83. Illustrations of endosoma sclerites (dorsal and lateral views) and paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males). 72 – 74. M. astictus sp. nov.; 75 – 77. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 78 – 80. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 81 – 83. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269722/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">77</figureCitation>
); the laterally constricted female abdominal sternite VII, with the apical half forming a halfround lobe, and the caudal margin without median notch (Fig. 
<number box="[854,885,404,429]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="36.0">36</number>
), are the diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName box="[1236,1395,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falciformis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1236,1395,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">M. falciformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="11" pageNumber="370" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="370" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,527,476,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">Description. Apterous male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[542,636,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 20" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1737,1759]" captionTargetBox="[225,1362,417,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[209,1378,409,1716]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 20. Habitus of Metrocoris spp. (apterous males). 13 – 16. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (13: Qingchen mountain; 14: Laojun mountain; 15: Xinmin village; 16: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 17. M. astictus sp. nov.; 18. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 19. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 20. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269715/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">Figs. 18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[649,681,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,524,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1403,517,1753]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 28. Photographs of bodies of apterous morph of Metrocoris spp. in dorsal view (males). 21 – 24. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (21: Qingchen mountain; 22: Laojun mountain; 23: Xinmin village; 24: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 25. M. astictus sp. nov.; 26. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 27. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 28. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269716/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">26</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<number box="[846,961,476,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="6.845" valueMax="6.88" valueMin="6.81">6.81–6.88</number>
, body width (across acetabula) 
<number box="[1317,1433,476,500]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="3.05" valueMax="3.09" valueMin="3.01">3.01–3.09</number>
. Colour: dorsum yellow with prominent black stripes; interocular dark mark usually arrowhead-shaped, bifid posteriorly, with narrow dark line along inner margin of eyes; first antennal segment yellowish brown, remaining segments usually blackish; rostrum yellowish with black apex; pronotum with T-shaped black stripe, lateral pronotal stripe very broad; mesonotum with slender longitudinal median stripe, sublateral stripes broader than lateral stripes, nearly equal in width to transverse bands; longitudinal dark stripe of mesopleuron slender, running at least 
<number box="[209,223,692,716]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[233,245,692,716]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="3.0">3</number>
of its length, very close to anterior margin but far from short acetabular mark; anterior transverse stripe of metanotum laterally confluent with posterior stripe of metanotum; fore femora with apical dark ring and four longitudinal marks, ventral mark connected with ring, remaining marks not confluent, inner mark pale and bright, external mark broad and blackish brown; middle and hind femora yellowish, tibiae and tarsi black; abdomen mainly blackish dorsally, abdominal tergites II–V blackish, abdominal tergites VI–VII blackish anteriorly and yellowish posteriorly; abdominal segment VIII with a large sub-rectangular blackish mark in dorsal view. Genital segments yellowish. Structural characters: head length 
<number box="[794,909,908,933]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="0.6950000000000001" valueMax="0.71" valueMin="0.68">0.68–0.71</number>
, head width 
<number box="[1064,1179,908,933]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="1.68" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="1.66">1.66–1.70</number>
, minimum interocular width 
<number box="[224,339,943,968]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="0.645" valueMax="0.66" valueMin="0.63">0.63–0.66</number>
; antenna about 
<number box="[520,569,944,968]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="0.83">0.83</number>
times as long as body, lengths of antennal segments I–IV: 
<number box="[1250,1302,943,968]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="2.65">2.65</number>
, 
<number box="[1315,1366,944,968]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="1.31">1.31</number>
, 
<number box="[1380,1432,944,968]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="1.1">1.10</number>
, 
<number box="[151,204,980,1005]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="0.62">0.62</number>
; pronotum slightly narrower than head, pronotum length 
<number box="[857,972,980,1005]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="0.765" valueMax="0.78" valueMin="0.75">0.75–0.78</number>
, pronotum width 
<number box="[1175,1290,980,1004]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="1.9049999999999998" valueMax="1.92" valueMin="1.89">1.89–1.92</number>
; fore femora moderately incrassate (
<figureCitation box="[410,494,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[178,1406,1766,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[173,1413,1764,1921]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Line drawings of fore legs of Metrocoris spp. (males) in lateral view. 39. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 40. M. astictus sp. nov.; 41. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 42. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 43. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269718/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">
Fig. 
<number box="[463,494,1016,1040]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
), ratio length/width 
<number box="[721,759,1016,1040]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="4.9">4.9</number>
, inner side not modified, with a subapical indentation, and a small single apical tooth (
<figureCitation box="[453,540,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[178,1406,1766,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[173,1413,1764,1921]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Line drawings of fore legs of Metrocoris spp. (males) in lateral view. 39. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 40. M. astictus sp. nov.; 41. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 42. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 43. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269718/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">
Fig. 
<number box="[509,540,1052,1076]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
); inner surface of fore tibiae not modified (
