<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="370" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1735,1760]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName box="[585,706,1736,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falciformis">
<emphasis box="[585,706,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">falciformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (from Latin, meaning acinaciform) refers to blade of paramere curved upwards and acinaciform-shaped.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="371" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,2013]" box="[199,654,1807,1832]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1807,1832]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,426,1807,1832]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">China</collectingCountry>
(Sichuan) (
<figureCitation box="[557,641,1807,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 84" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1006,1028]" captionTargetBox="[158,1426,202,978]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,984]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 84. Geographical distribution of Metrocoris spp. in this study." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269723/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">
Fig. 
<number box="[609,641,1808,1832]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="84.0">84</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,2013]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1437,151,248]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="371" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,426,1844,1869]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">Comparative notes</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[441,600,1844,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falciformis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[441,600,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">M. falciformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[608,698,1844,1869]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[608,698,1844,1869]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
fits the diagnostic characters of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1108,1241,1844,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lituratus">
<emphasis box="[1108,1241,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">M. lituratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[186,438,1879,1904]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" refString="Chen, P. P. &amp; Nieser, N. (1993) A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Part I &amp; II. Steenstrupia, 19, 1 - 43, 45 - 82." type="journal article" year="1993">
Chen &amp; Nieser (
<number box="[368,429,1880,1904]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="1993.0">1993</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The general appearance of this new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993" authorityName="Chen &amp; Nieser" authorityYear="1993" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis box="[1076,1256,1880,1904]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">M. sichuanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" refString="Chen, P. P. &amp; Nieser, N. (1993) A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Part I &amp; II. Steenstrupia, 19, 1 - 43, 45 - 82." type="journal article" year="1993">
Chen &amp; Nieser, 
<number box="[151,210,1916,1940]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the paramere blade of 
<taxonomicName box="[596,756,1916,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falciformis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[596,756,1916,1940]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">M. falciformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[765,856,1916,1941]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[765,856,1916,1941]" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is falciform-shaped, with the lateral part bearing a distinctly angular projection, and its blade apex narrowed (
<figureCitation box="[829,925,1952,1977]" captionStart="FIGURES 59 – 66" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,1438,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[175,1411,1430,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 59 – 66. Paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males) in external view. 59 – 62. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (59: Qingchen mountain; 60: Laojun mountain; 61: Xinmin village; 62: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 63. M. astictus sp. nov.; 64. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 65. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 66. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269720/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">Figs. 64</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[939,970,1952,1976]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 83" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,887,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[205,1381,876,1821]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 83. Illustrations of endosoma sclerites (dorsal and lateral views) and paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males). 72 – 74. M. astictus sp. nov.; 75 – 77. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 78 – 80. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 81 – 83. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269722/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">77</figureCitation>
), while in 
<taxonomicName box="[1096,1278,1952,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis box="[1096,1278,1952,1976]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="370">M. sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the paramere blade is relatively slender and straight, without an angular projection laterally, and the blade apex is slightly extended (
<figureCitation box="[268,349,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1240,1262]" captionTargetBox="[261,1319,180,1214]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[255,1332,171,1228]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Photograph of Metrocoris sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (holotype, male) and illustration of diagnostic characters. 1. Habitus of holotype; 2. Related labels; 3. Male fore leg in lateral view; 4. Endosoma sclerites in dorsolateral view; 5. Paramere in external view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269713/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
, 
